init_text: You're Barack Obama. 4 years into your retirement, you awake to find a letter with no return address on your bedside table. It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: But you can't shake the feeling that it's real.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: To your surprise, it's a real number.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: As you place the call, you can't help feeling that your life is about to change forever.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The voice on the other end of the line is familiar...it's John F. Kennedy!

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Then he says "Don't worry Barack, I know you're shocked...I'd be too if I were in your shoes.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You book the first flight to the Caribbean you can find.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You arrive at JFK's private island.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He's already there waiting for you.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You are beside yourself with excitement.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: What a strange and fantastic thing to experience!

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It involves creating a new superpower that will rival the United States of America.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: JFK has already drawn up the plans for the superpower in his lab.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He tells you that they'll take it from there.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You promise them that the superpower is a good idea and will in fact motivate the U.S.
